<P>A Pro&s;pect OF Eternity.</P>
<P>WHEREIN Is Clearly Proved,
<LIST>
<ITEM>I. That there is an Eternity into which all Men mu&s;t enter, when they go out of Time.</ITEM>
<ITEM>II. That we &s;hould Eye Eternity, and look at Eternal Things.</ITEM>
<ITEM>III. That this looking ought to have an Influence upon us, in all that we do.</ITEM>
</LIST></P>
<P><HI>By</HI> THO. DOOLITTLE.</P>
<Q><BIBL><HI>Matt. 25.46.</HI></BIBL>
<P>And the&s;e &s;hall go away into Everla&s;ting Puni&s;h|ment: But the Righteous into Life Eternal.</P></Q>
<P><HI>Bo&s;ton:</HI> Printed by <HI>T. Fleet</HI> and <HI>T. Crump,</HI> for <HI>Nicholas Buttolph,</HI> at the lower End of <HI>Corn-Hill.</HI> 1715.</P>
